commentary: Cremer to Mahmudullah, no run Bangladesh are falling away. Dragged short, Mahmudullah chops it towards covers and sets off.. Mashrafe, however, isn't interested. The fielder fires a bulls-eye throw, Mahmudullah is gone.... Oh wait, what do we have here? Drama! Chakabva breaks the stumps (accidentally) with his gloves before the direct hit thudded into the furniture. Mahmudullah survives. They check for a front-foot no ball now. It is fine. Mahmudullah joins his captain. Chigumbura does not look happy. He has a chat with umpire Dar. More drama here! Another angle shows that Chakabva had belatedly remedied his error, calling for the ball off the ricochet, and knocking a stump out . Is the play dead? Looks so. Umpire Dar has a chat with the TV umpire. Chigumbura then intervenes. The final verdict is NOT OUT.
shortText: Cremer to Mahmudullah, no run
text: Bangladesh are falling away. Dragged short, Mahmudullah chops it towards covers and sets off.. Mashrafe, however, isn't interested. The fielder fires a bulls-eye throw, Mahmudullah is gone.... Oh wait, what do we have here? Drama! Chakabva breaks the stumps (accidentally) with his gloves before the direct hit thudded into the furniture. Mahmudullah survives. They check for a front-foot no ball now. It is fine. Mahmudullah joins his captain. Chigumbura does not look happy. He has a chat with umpire Dar. More drama here! Another angle shows that Chakabva had belatedly remedied his error, calling for the ball off the ricochet, and knocking a stump out . Is the play dead? Looks so. Umpire Dar has a chat with the TV umpire. Chigumbura then intervenes. The final verdict is NOT OUT.

commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to Sikandar Raza, OUT Sabbir plucks out a stunner after missing one earlier. He lands on his elbow again, but hangs on. Raza is sent packing. Nice and full on middle, Raza seeks to flick but loops it to the off side off a leading edge. Sabbir runs to his left from mid-on, dives full stretch to his left, snapping it up near the mid-off region. He takes his cap off and celebrates!

commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to Jongwe, OUT Mustafiz engineers a double-strike. Sabbir has another. Full again, Jongwe stretches forward for a sweep but can only mis-hit it. Sabbir takes a much easier catch at midwicket

commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to Panyangara, OUT Is that a return catch? Mustafiz claims the catch. They go upstairs. Whippy cutter from Mustafiz, Panyangara is early into the drive and spoons it back. It isn't a bump ball. The noise came from the bat jamming the turf. Third five-for in ODIs for Mustafiz in only his ninth game

commentary: Arafat Sunny to Muzarabani, OUT That is that! Bangladesh sweep the series 3-0, they win the final ODI by 61 runs. Loopier and drifts in, another soft dismissal, sums up the story for Zimbabwe. Feebly chipped back to the bowler
